Repository Name Unauthorized: Maitland Historical Museum and Telephone Museum
Notes: Documents the history and life of small town Florida. Includes cemetery and early City records, photographs, obituaries, voter registration information and the Waterhouse, Hill, and Dommerich family archives.The Telephone Museum collection includes telephones, equipment, and archives representing the story of the Galloway family who started telephone service in this area and  the story of the rise of Winter Park Telephone Company.
